data.title: Songs with girls' names in the title
data.meta_description: Songfacts category - Songs with girls' names in the title
data.text:
Give It AwayRed Hot Chili Peppers

If what you get equals what you give away, you might as well give it all away. That's the concept behind "Give It Away" by Red Hot Chili Peppers.

Hey Ya!OutKast

Outkast's "Hey Ya" was the first song in history to rack up 1 million downloads.

One WeekBarenaked Ladies

"One Week" by Barenaked Ladies was a #1 hit in America - for exactly one week in 1998.

Take Me Home Country RoadsJohn Denver

"Take Me Home Country Roads" is set in West Virginia, but John Denver had never been there when he recorded the song. The country roads represent a sense of belonging.

Mr. Tambourine ManBob Dylan

Bob Dylan's original version of "Mr. Tambourine Man," released on his album Bringing It All Back Home, has no tambourine, just guitars and harmonica.

Midnight Train To GeorgiaGladys Knight & the Pips

"Midnight Train To Georgia" was originally "Midnight Plane To Houston," but was changed to sound more R&B.

90s MetalFact or Fiction

Test your metal - Priest, Maiden, and Beavis and Butt-head show up in this one.

Adam Young of Owl CitySongwriter Interviews

Is Owl City on a quest for another hit like "Fireflies?" Adam answers that question and explains the influences behind many others.

Chris Robinson of The Black CrowesSongwriter Interviews

"Great songwriters don't necessarily have hit songs," says Chris. He's written a bunch, but his fans are more interested in the intricate jams.

Famous Singers' First FilmsSong Writing

A look at the good (Diana Ross, Eminem), the bad (Madonna, Bob Dylan) and the peculiar (David Bowie, Michael Jackson) film debuts of superstar singers.
